0Zionism%20as%20yet%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eanother%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20accommodating%20thereby%20the%20inherently%20anti-Semitic%20claim%20that%20the%20Jewish%20people%20did%20not%20belong%20in%20the%20West%20but%20in%20Palestine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELong%20after%20his%20death%20this%20has%20enabled%20the%20West%20to%20minimise%20its%20responsibility%20for%20Shoah.%20Today%2C%20when%20Israel%20bombs%20Gaza%2C%20it%20is%20in%20fact%20the%20West%20that%20does%20so.%20And%20the%20West%20it%20is%20that%20admonishes%20bewildered%20Palestinians%20as%20they%20die%2C%20%E2%80%9CNever%20again!%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%2C%20thereafter%2C%20in%20terrorising%20the%20Arab%20and%20the%20Muslim%20world%2C%20the%20West%20terrorises%20at%20the%20same%20time%20Israelis%2C%20placing%20them%20forever%20as%20anxious%20local%20gendarmerie%2C%20ever%20threatened%2C%20ever%20dependent%20on%20Western%20largesse%2C%20forever%20denied%20the%20possibility%20of%20real%20freedom.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAndrew%20Handler%2C%20wartime%20member%20of%20the%20Zionist%20youth%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMaccabi%20ha-Za%E2%80%99ir%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0has%20shown%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDori%3A%20The%20Life%20%26amp%3B%20Times%20of%20Theodor%20Herzl%20in%20Budapest%201860-1878%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EUniversity%20of%20Alabama%20Press%2C%201983)%20how%20the%20campaign%20for%20an%20ethnic%20Magyar-dominated%20Hungarian%20Kingdom%20had%20made%20up%20the%20lie%20that%20rule%20from%20Vienna%20had%20enabled%20the%20Jews%20to%20rob%20the%20Hungarian%20people.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%20this%20very%20anti-Semitism%20was%20to%20inspire%2C%20paradoxically%2C%20as%20Handler%20has%20argued%2C%20the%20Zionist%20programme%20itself.%20On%20June%2024%2C%201878%2C%20Gy%C5%91z%C5%91%C2%A0%C2%A0Ist%C3%B3czy%20set%20out%20in%20the%20Hungarian%20Diet%20that%20the%20Jews%20would%20destroy%20Hungary%20and%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%9Csolution%C2%A0is%20none%20other%20than%20the%20restoration%20of%20the%20ancient%20Jewish%20state%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Jewish%20Question%20was%20a%20national%20one%2C%20he%20said%2C%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eestablishment%20in%20Palestine%20of%20an%20independent%20Jewish%20state%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHandler%20points%20out%20the%20%E2%80%9Cstriking%20similarity%20between%20key%20passages%20of%20Istoczy%E2%80%99s%20anti-Semitic%20screed%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20Palesztina%20Beszcd%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0Herzl%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EDer%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EJudenstaat%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20laying%20out%20the%20ideology%20of%20the%20future%20state%20of%20Israel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20Herzl%20decided%20that%20the%20Jewish%20peoples%20of%20Europe%20could%20only%20gain%20safety%20by%20creating%20their%20own%20ethnic%20nationalism%2C%20%26amp%3B%20so%20adopted%20the%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eanti-Semitic%20demand%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0that%20Palestine%20become%20the%20Jewish%20homeland.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%20Herzl%E2%80%99s%20Zionism%20%26amp%3B%20the%20policy%20to%20which%20it%20led%2C%20namely%20the%20Balfour%20Declaration%2C%20was%20opposed%20by%20liberal%20Western%20Jews%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbalfourproject.org%2Fedwin-montagu-and-zionism-1917%5C%22%3EBritish%20statesman%20Edwin%20Montagu%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20wish%20to%20place%20on%20record%20my%20view%20that%20the%20policy%20of%20His%20Majesty%E2%80%99s%20Government%20is%20anti-Semitic%20and%20in%20result%20will%20prove%20a%20rallying%20ground%20for%20Anti-Semites%20in%20every%20country%20in%20the%20world%E2%80%A6I%20assert%20that%20there%20is%20not%20a%20Jewish%20nation%E2%80%A6When%20the%20Jews%20are%20told%20that%20Palestine%20is%20their%20national%20home%2C%20every%20country%20will%20immediately%20desire%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20its%20Jewish%20citizens%2C%20and%20you%20will%20find%20a%20population%20in%20Palestine%20driving%20out%20its%20present%20inhabitants%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENevertheless%2C%20the%20new%20ethnic%20nationalisms%20spread%20rapidly%2C%20each%20ethnic%20majority%20seeking%20to%20award%20itself%20a%20territory%20and%20the%20state%20that%20went%20with%20it%2C%20promoting%20mutually%20exclusive%20extravagant%20claims%20intolerant%20of%20those%20outside%20the%20mythical%20%E2%80%9Cnation%E2%80%9D%2C%20all%20seized%20by%20the%20identical%20Hobbesian%20paranoia%20about%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eoutsiders%20within.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ELook%20to%20India%20to%20see%20how%20this%20travelled%3A%20for%20Vinayak%20Damodar%20Savarkar%20who%20did%20much%20to%20shape%20the%20Indian%20ideology%20of%20today%20justified%20what%20Hitler%20was%20doing%20shortly%20before%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EKristallnacht%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESeveral%20communities%20may%20live%20in%20one%20country%20for%20thousands%20of%20years%20but%20this%20does%20not%20help%20in%20forming%20a%20nation%E2%80%A6In%20Germany%20the%20movement%20of%20the%20Germans%20is%20the%20national%20movement%20but%20that%20of%20the%20Jews%20is%20a%20communal%20one.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESavarkar%E2%80%99s%20speech%20was%C2%A0reported%C2%A0in%20the%20weekly%20confidential%20(Intelligence)%20report%20to%20the%20District%20Magistrate%20Poona%2C%20October%201938%C2%A0.%20He%20then%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20elaborated%20on%20this%20to%20students%20of%20the%20Law%20College%2C%20Poona%20in%20July%201939%2C%20before%20hostilities%20commenced%20in%20World%20War%20II%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9CNationality%20did%20not%20depend%20so%20much%20on%20a%20common%20geographical%20area%20as%20on%20unity%20of%20thought%2C%20religion%2C%20language%20and%20culture.%20For%20this%20reason%20the%20Germans%20and%20Jews%20could%20not%20be%20regarded%20as%20one%20nation.%20%3Cem%3EIn%20the%20same%20way%20India%20was%20a%20nation%20of%20Hindus%20as%20they%20were%20in%20the%20majority%3C%2Fem%3E%20(emphasis%20added%2C%20Bombay%20Province%20Weekly%20Letter%2C%20No.%2020%2C%20September%2030%2C%201939).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAuthoritarian%20variants%20produced%20distinct%20European%20fascisms%3A%20although%20Germany%20is%20the%20most%20cited%2C%20we%20might%20look%20to%20France%2C%20turning%20in%20on%20itself%20after%20defeat%20at%20Sedan%20and%20the%20Paris%20Commune%20to%20look%20for%20an%20%E2%80%9Cenemy%20within%E2%80%9D%20when%20it%20persecuted%20Alfred%20Dreyfus.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20that%20falsehood%20being%20exposed%2C%20anti-Semitism%20persisted%2C%20fortified%20by%20the%20colonial%20racism%20common%20to%20most%20European%20states%3B%20so%20years%20later%20it%20powered%20popular%20support%20for%20Petain%20%26amp%3B%20his%20Vichy%20collaboration%20with%20National%20Socialism%2C%20which%20rounded%20up%20Jews%20to%20send%20them%20off%20to%20be%20tortured%20and%20murdered%2C%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ERafle%20du%20Vel%E2%80%99%20d%E2%80%99Hiv%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eat%20the%20cycling%20stadium%20in%20Paris%20in%20July%201942.%20Maurice%20Papon%2C%20one%20of%20its%20high%20functionaries%2C%20was%20like%20most%20never%20punished%3B%20accordingly%2C%20he%20was%20to%20go%20on%20to%20torture%20Algerians%20and%20detain%20them%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Esame%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20stadium%20in%20Paris%20in%201961%20and%20organise%20their%20murder.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Insufficiently%20acknowledged%2C%20this%20very%20anti-Semitism%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ereborn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20today%20as%20Islamophobia%2C%20serving%20to%20appease%20both%20traditional%20anti-Semites%20as%20well%20as%20survivors%20of%20genocide.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20such%20French%20tradition%20that%20accounts%20for%20the%20surreal%20spectacle%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20Sephardic%C2%A0%C3%89ric%20Zemmour%C2%A0reassuring%20the%20French%20that%20their%20ancestors%20had%20no%20responsibility%20for%20Shoah%2C%20even%20as%20his%20fellow%20right%20wing%20colleague%20Marine%20Le%20Pen%20supports%20Israel%20yet%20is%20silent%20on%20her%20own%20family%E2%80%99s%20rich%20anti-Semitic%20history%3B%20as%20well%20as%20the%20absurdity%20of%20how%20the%20%E2%80%9Chijab%20question%E2%80%9D%20has%20now%20become%20the%20central%20concern%20of%20French%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ela%C3%AFcit%C3%A9%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20rapidly%20o%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eccidentalising%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20Jews%20whom%20it%20so%20recently%20orientalised%2C%20and%20orientalising%20instead%20Muslims%2C%20consistent%20with%20the%20creation%20of%20%E2%80%9Canti-Semitism%E2%80%9D%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20concern%20as%20entirely%20distinct%20from%20other%20racism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMight%20we%20not%20therefore%20see%20Zionism%20itself%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enot%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20a%20lobby%20that%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20impedes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20US%20strategic%20concerns%2C%20but%20a%20subordinate%20agent%20that%20enacts%20them%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Elimiting%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20thereby%20its%20own%20agency%3F%20We%20might%20recall%20that%20during%20the%20Suez%20Crisis%20the%20British%20MP%20Nye%20Bevan%20had%20focused%20on%20those%20responsible%20for%20the%20debacle%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20we%20complain%20about%20the%20tune%2C%20there%20is%20no%20reason%20to%20criticise%20the%20monkey%20when%20the%20organ-grinder%20is%20present%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(House%20of%20Commons%20Debates%2C%20May%2016%2C%201957)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%C2%A0%20it%20is%20not%20%E2%80%9CJewish%20control%20of%20the%20media%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20that%20conspiratorial%20anti-Semitic%20fantasy%20that%20serves%20some%20as%20well%20as%20Islamophobia%20%E2%80%93%20but%20Western%20policy%2C%20specifically%20American%2C%20which%20defines%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIsrael%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20safeguarding%20its%20interest%20in%20controlling%20petroleum%20and%C2%A0%20international%20waterways%2C%20which%20accounts%20for%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20acts%20today.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKannan%20Srinivasan%20is%20at%20Wertheim%20Study%20New%20York%20Public%20Library%20and%20can%20be%20reached%20at%20kannansrinivasan%40icloud.com.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3ESrinivasan%20is%20grateful%20for%20inspiration%20from%20Catherine%20Benoit%2C%20Akeel%20Bilgrami%2C%20Faisal%20Devji%2C%20Gowri%20Gurumurthy%2C%20Carol%20Krinsky%20and%20Sanjay%20Reddy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cb%3E%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711276618000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F24160515%2FGJCsC8XWgAABpvH.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fanti-semitism-palestinians-and-the-west-a-historical-background-of-the-current-bombing-of-gaza%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20is%20western%20policy%20that%20defines%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20safeguarding%20its%20interest%20which%20accounts%20for%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20acts%20today.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fanti-semitism-palestinians-and-the-west-a-historical-background-of-the-current-bombing-of-gaza%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Where%20Are%20the%20'Don%20Quixotes'%20of%20Indian%20Academia%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F05%2F29112534%2Fcensorship.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20almost%20two%20years%E2%80%A6%20again%20I%20got%20blessed%20with%20the%20mercy%20(from%20whom%2C%20you%20guess).%20This%20is%20the%20third%20time%20in%20the%20last%206%20years%20that%20I%20am%20leaving%20my%20job.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20morning%20began%20with%20this%20message%20from%20Mukesh%20Kumar%2C%20a%20friend%20and%20journalist.%20Kumar%20was%20a%20teacher%20and%20dean%20in%20the%20media%20and%20communication%20department%20of%20Lovely%20University%20in%20Jalandhar%20for%20about%20two%20years.%20Yesterday%2C%20he%20resigned%20from%20his%20job.%20Or%20was%20made%20to%20resign.%20His%20employer%2C%20the%20university%2C%20felt%20that%20his%20presence%20on%20the%20campus%20was%20harmful%20to%20its%20interests%20and%20he%20should%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20third%20job%20he%20has%20had%20to%20leave%20in%20these%20last%206%20years%2C%20said%20Kumar.%20Before%20Lovely%20University%2C%20he%20had%20been%20removed%20from%20Shri%20Guru%20Gobind%20Singh%20Tricentenary%20University%20(SGT%20University)%2C%20Gurgaon%20and%20Makhanlal%20Chaturvedi%20Journalism%20University%2C%20Bhopal.%20It%20is%20not%20very%20difficult%20to%20understand%20why%20he%20had%20to%20leave%20these%20institutions.%20Kumar%20dislikes%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20and%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cmark%3E%3C%2Fmark%3EKumar%20is%20a%20face%20well%20recognised%20by%20Hindi-speaking%20viewers.%20Everyone%20remembers%20his%20literary%20discussion%20%E2%80%98Subah%20Savere%E2%80%99%20with%20Namvar%20Singh%20on%20Doordarshan.%20The%20talk%20shows%20and%20discussions%20he%20conducts%20on%20contemporary%20political%20and%20social%20issues%20on%20the%20platform%20of%20%E2%80%98Satya%20Hindi%E2%80%99%20are%20very%20popular.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKumar%20talks%20calmly.%20But%20he%20has%20firm%20secular%20and%20democratic%20values.%20It%20becomes%20natural%20then%20for%20a%20person%20like%20him%20to%20be%20critical%20of%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20RSS.%20He%20does%20not%20pretend%20to%20be%20impartial%2C%20which%20is%20what%20many%20journalists%20claim%20to%20be%20when%20they%20tolerate%20the%20majoritarian%20ideology%20of%20the%20BJP%20or%20the%20RSS.%20They%20claim%20that%20they%20do%20not%20take%20sides%20between%20secularism%20and%20communalism.%20They%20have%20a%20duty%20to%20only%20report%20the%20battle%20between%20these%20two%20ideologies.%20It%20is%20as%20if%20they%20are%20reporting%20a%20wrestling%20match%20where%20they%20are%20mere%20observers.%20Kumar%20does%20not%20belong%20to%20this%20league%20of%20journalists.%20One%20can%20understand%20that%20a%20journalist%20should%20not%20be%20biased%20in%20favour%20of%20any%20political%20party%20in%20his%20journalism%20but%20he%20must%20be%20partisan%20towards%20the%20values%20of%20civility%20and%20refinement.%20Otherwise%2C%20why%20pursue%20journalism%20at%20all%3F%20And%20we%20know%20that%20the%20ideology%20of%20the%20BJP%20and%20RSS%20is%20opposed%20to%20civility%20or%20refinement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20considers%20journalists%20like%20Kumar%20as%20its%20enemies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Lovely%20University%20invited%20him%2C%20it%20knew%20his%20history.%20The%20institute%20was%20also%20familiar%20with%20his%20views.%20Being%20secular%2C%20you%20will%20definitely%20be%20an%20opponent%20or%20critic%20of%20BJP%20or%20RSS.%20Aware%20of%20all%20this%2C%20Lovely%20University%20chose%20to%C2%A0%20invite%20him%20as%20a%20faculty%20member.%20Why%20did%20it%20then%20ask%20him%20to%20go%20now%3F%20Or%20will%20it%20say%20that%20he%20left%20voluntarily%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20coming%20to%20the%20university%2C%20Kumar%20had%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20he%20would%20not%20leave%20his%20journalism.%20He%20would%20not%20stop%20his%20talk%20shows.%20The%20management%20had%20no%20objection%20to%20his%20condition.%20Why%20did%20it%20now%20ask%20him%20to%20stop%20his%20shows%20to%20be%20able%20to%C2%A0%20continue%20in%20the%20university%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20difficult%20to%20understand%20the%20reason%20why%20it%20happened%20now.%20Elections%20are%20close%20and%20BJP%20wants%20to%20silence%20all%20its%20critics.%20Lovely%20University%20cannot%20afford%20enmity%20with%20BJP%20at%20this%20stage.%20Its%20patron%20is%20a%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20from%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP).%20They%20know%20how%20heavy%20the%20cost%20of%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20anger%20can%20be%20for%20them.%20What%20do%20they%20lose%20if%20they%20sacrifice%20Kumar%20for%20their%20safety%3F%20After%20all%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20we%20remember%20what%20Ashoka%20University%20did%20to%20Pratap%20Bhanu%20Mehta%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20there%20is%20only%20one%20condition%20for%20the%20survival%20of%20institutions%3A%20declaration%20of%20loyalty%20to%20the%20BJP%20government.%20If%20you%20do%20not%20do%20it%20then%2C%20at%20the%20very%20least%2C%20you%20should%20be%20silent.%20Kumar%E2%80%99s%20outspokenness%20could%20have%20been%20dangerous%20for%20the%20administrators%20of%20Lovely%20University.%20He%20faced%20a%20choice%3A%20stop%20his%20program%20and%20remain%20at%20the%20university%2C%20or%20continue%20speaking%20and%20lose%20the%20job.%20Kumar%20chose%20his%20voice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20choice%20is%20bound%20to%20cause%20economic%20insecurity%20to%20him.%20But%20what%20should%20one%20do%20when%20asked%20to%20choose%20between%20freedom%20and%20security%3F%20Kumar%20has%20answered%20it.%20He%20remains%20what%20he%20was.%20Unlike%20him%2C%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20Lovely%20University%20lost%20its%20right%20to%20be%20called%20a%20university%3F%20It%20can%20be%20said%20that%20the%20presence%20or%20absence%20of%20one%20person%20does%20not%20make%20much%20difference%20to%20any%20institution.%20But%20the%20reason%20for%20which%20he%20had%20to%20leave%20tells%20us%20whether%20the%20university%20is%20able%20to%20fulfil%20its%20dharma%20or%20not.%20That%20dharma%20is%20to%20provide%20and%20create%20open%20space%20for%20free%20thoughts.%20If%20the%20university%20prevents%20you%20from%20expressing%20your%20views%20publicly%2C%20then%20it%20is%20defeating%20its%20purpose.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20important%20to%20reiterate%20that%20one%20of%20the%20tasks%20of%20academics%20is%20to%20constantly%20communicate%20with%20society%20so%20that%20it%20can%20understand%20itself%20better%20and%20also%20think%20about%20and%20what%20is%20happening%20to%20it.%20Teachers%20provide%20society%20with%20facts%20and%20also%20make%20available%20conceptual%20tools%2C%20with%20the%20help%20of%20which%20it%20can%20analyse%20events%20and%20situations.%20This%20is%20the%20social%20responsibility%20of%20the%20teacher.%20Those%20who%20say%20that%20teachers%20should%20only%20be%20concerned%20with%20their%20classroom%20and%20limit%20themselves%20to%20the%20task%20of%20completing%20the%20syllabus%2C%20do%20not%20know%20anything%20about%20the%20role%20of%20teachers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20happened%20to%20Kumar%20is%20happening%20quietly%20in%20other%20universities%2C%20especially%20the%20private%20universities%2C%20and%20we%20are%20often%20not%20aware%20of%20it.%20Private%20universities%20hire%20teachers%20in%20subjects%20such%20as%20journalism%20or%20mass%20communication%20on%20short-term%20contracts.%20It%20is%20their%20choice%20whether%20to%20continue%20the%20contract%20or%20not.%20But%20we%20have%20been%20hearing%20about%20the%20contracts%20of%20temporary%20teachers%2C%20who%20are%20considered%20inconvenient%20for%20the%20BJP%2C%20not%20being%20renewed%20or%20terminated.%20It%20is%20difficult%20for%20all%20such%20teachers%20to%20go%20public%20with%20this%20information%20for%20obvious%20reasons.%20It%20might%20affect%20their%20chances%20of%20employment%20at%20a%20new%20place.%20No%20institution%20would%20like%20to%20hire%20a%20person%20disagreeable%20to%20the%20regime.%20So%20most%20of%20them%20keep%20quiet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20easy%20for%20the%20government%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20private%20universities.%20Their%20patrons%20are%20usually%20industrialists%20and%20businessmen.%20The%20government%20can%20attack%20their%20business%20on%20any%20pretext%20from%20questioning%20their%20land%20use%20to%20disconnecting%20water%20or%20electricity%20supply%20and%20withdrawing%20permission%20for%20new%20buildings%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECan%20any%20institution%20afford%20so%20much%20trouble%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20the%20freedom%20of%20public%20expression%20of%20one%20teacher%3F%20So%20even%20though%20patrons%20with%20good%20intentions%20tell%20teachers%20that%20they%20have%20complete%20freedom%20in%20their%20classes%2C%20they%20should%20keep%20their%20mouths%20shut%20outside.%20At%20least%20it%20will%20save%20the%20university.%20This%20is%20why%20you%20will%20hardly%20see%20articles%20on%20%E2%80%98sensitive%20topics%E2%80%99%20private%20university%20teachers%20in%20newspapers%20and%20other%20media%20platforms.%20It%20is%20not%20that%20they%20have%20changed%20their%20views%20or%20are%20scared.%20They%20have%20gone%20silent%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20their%20organisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20is%20not%20happening%20at%20Delhi%20University%20right%20now%2C%20the%20government%20is%20trying%20to%20change%20the%20service%20conditions%20of%20teachers%20and%20put%20restrictions%20on%20their%20public%20writing%20or%20activity.%20Many%20central%20institutions%20have%20done%20this.%20This%20step%20gets%20support%20in%20the%20society%20because%20there%20is%20a%20general%20understanding%20that%20those%20who%20get%20salaries%20from%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20money%20do%20not%20have%20the%20right%20to%20criticise%20the%20government.%20But%20this%20understanding%20itself%20is%20flawed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPublic%20resources%20should%20be%20used%20in%20public%20interest.%20There%20is%20always%20a%20tension%20between%20public%20interest%20and%20power.%20Often%2C%20those%20in%20power%20force%20the%20public%20to%20consider%20their%20own%20interest%20as%20public%20interest.%20It%20is%20the%20job%20of%20those%20working%20in%20the%20field%20of%20knowledge%20production%20to%20keep%20the%20public%20aware%20of%20this%20tension%20and%20conflict.%20Their%20public%20speaking%20or%20writing%20is%20necessary%2C%20not%20for%20themselves%2C%20but%20for%20the%20interest%20of%20the%20public.%20How%20else%20will%20the%20facts%20given%20by%20the%20government%20and%20the%20reasons%20given%20for%20its%20decisions%20be%20tested%20or%20judged%3F%20This%20is%20where%20academics%20have%20a%20role%20to%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20surprising%20that%20the%20relations%20between%20those%20in%20power%20and%20intellectuals%20are%20not%20generally%20cordial.%20But%20a%20totalitarian%20ideology%20considers%20them%20as%20its%20enemies.%20That%20is%20what%20we%E2%80%99re%20seeing%20in%20India%20right%20now.%20The%20government%20does%20not%20want%20to%20allow%20any%20other%20voice%20in%20the%20country%20except%20their%20own.%20Certainly%20not%20the%20calm%2C%20civilised%20and%20reasoned%20voice%20of%20a%20person%20like%20Kumar%20who%20chose%20freedom%20of%20his%20voice%20over%20his%20job.%20What%20did%20Lovely%20University%20choose%3F%20And%20do%20his%20students%20realise%20what%20has%20been%20taken%20away%20from%20them%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Fbyline%2Fapoorvanand%5C%22%3EApoorvanand%3C%2Fa%3E%20teaches%20at%20Delhi%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711276046000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F201